l to do justice to the poet's astonishing radicality. Readers will not only come away with a new appreciation of Hölderlin's poetic and political-theoretical achievements but will also discover the motivating force behind Hamacher's own achievements as a literary scholar and political theorist. An introduction by Julia Ng and an afterword by Peter Fenves provide further information about these studies and the academic and theoretical context in which they were composed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aGerman poetryy19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aIdealism, German. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aBenjamin.  aDeconstruction.  aDerrida.  aGerman Idealism.  aGerman Romantic Poetry.  aHeidegger.  aHölderlin.  aSzondi.  aTheories of Meaning.  aTheories of Revolution.1 aAdler, Anthony Curtis.1 aFenves, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNg, Julia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNg, Julia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361112240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503611122423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503611122.jpg  a978-3-11-069218-1  SUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb